1
00:00:47,672 --> 00:00:50,967
THE APARTMENT JOB

2
00:00:53,052 --> 00:00:56,139
Let's do a solo shot
of the eldest son this time.

3
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:04,063
You already look so good.

4
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:05,814
I'll start shooting now.

5
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:07,983
One, two, three.

6
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,485
Hello.

7
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:10,695
You scared me.

8
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:13,739
You almost burst my eardrums,
you little brat.

9
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:15,283
One, two, three!

10
00:01:16,117 --> 00:01:19,036
That's great. You look so reliable.

11
00:01:19,037 --> 00:01:20,996
Can you smile a little?

12
00:01:20,997 --> 00:01:22,372
All right. One more shot.

13
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:23,999
One, two, three!

14
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:24,834
Nice.

15
00:01:26,211 --> 00:01:27,754
Stop playing with that.

16
00:01:30,298 --> 00:01:33,634
- I'm tired. Stop it.
- Hello!

17
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:36,179
- Hello.
- Stop.

18
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:40,850
<i>I'm going to win.</i>

19
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:43,227
<i>I'll win, no matter what.</i>

20
00:01:43,228 --> 00:01:46,856
<i>I'll win and save Yong-man
and protect my guys.</i>

21
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:48,566
<i>I'll make sure of it.</i>

22
00:01:50,985 --> 00:01:52,612
Here's our contract. Read it and sign it.

23
00:01:54,531 --> 00:01:56,449
You didn't need to write up a contract.

24
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:00,370
The photoshoot took way too long.

25
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:04,456
You should've at least given me food.
I've been starving…

26
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:07,251
Stop grumbling.
You're going to enjoy the food anyway.

27
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:08,086
Eat up.

28
00:02:09,003 --> 00:02:10,212
Excuse me.

29
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:12,047
"A penalty three times the amount issued

30
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,758
for termination due to Party B's fault?"

31
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:17,303
What could I possibly be at fault for?

32
00:02:18,179 --> 00:02:21,723
If the contract ever has to be terminated,
it would be your fault.

33
00:02:21,724 --> 00:02:24,811
I'm a professional when it comes to work.

34
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:28,605
So unfortunately,
we're going to have to cancel this.

35
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:30,692
If you do your job professionally,
there won't be…

36
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:33,570
- Remove that clause.
- Yes, sir.

37
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:39,241
Have you been to the rooftop?

38
00:02:39,242 --> 00:02:40,159
Hey, be quiet.

39
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,995
I had to go to the rooftop
to get that clause removed.

40
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,914
Your soup will get cold.
Just sign it and eat.

41
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:48,543
KANG HA-RI

42
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,005
It looks like a celebrity autograph.

43
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,214
All done, right?

44
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,049
Mr. Park.

45
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:58,552
I believe our meeting like this
can be called fate.

46
00:02:58,553 --> 00:03:01,263
They say people who live together
and eat together

47
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:02,556
are a family…

48
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:04,057
Shut it.

49
00:03:04,058 --> 00:03:05,934
Goodness. Excuse me.

50
00:03:05,935 --> 00:03:08,062
You shouldn't say that to your elders.

51
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:11,524
You keep calling him "excuse me."
He's Mr. Park.

52
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:14,777
Let's sort this out.

53
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:17,988
She's your sister-in-law now.
Call her Ms. Kang.

54
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,324
- Ms. Kang.
- Ms. Kang.

55
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:22,826
- And the Lizard…
- Lizard?

56
00:03:22,827 --> 00:03:23,953
Ha-ri, my daughter-in-law.

57
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:27,081
- Gyeong-buk.
- Mom!

58
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:31,377
And I'll call you "darling."

59
00:03:32,962 --> 00:03:34,713
I'm getting goosebumps.

60
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:37,007
How about just "honey"?

61
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,717
Fine by me.

62
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:40,552
Call my guys by their last name too.

63
00:03:40,553 --> 00:03:41,763
What?

64
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:46,934
This whole honorifics thing
in Korea is ridiculous.

65
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:50,145
They're supposed to be
my husband's younger brothers.

66
00:03:50,146 --> 00:03:52,649
Didn't you say you're a professional?

67
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:57,654
Mr. Kim, Mr. Jang, Mr. Kim.

68
00:03:59,572 --> 00:04:00,615
Happy?

69
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:03,368
- Let's eat.
- Yes, sir.

70
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:06,286
Shouldn't they address you properly too?

71
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:08,705
You're their older brother now.

72
00:04:08,706 --> 00:04:09,666
Aren't you brothers?

73
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:12,001
Right. It's been a while.

74
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:14,504
Treat me like your older brother now.

75
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,506
Really?

76
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:18,590
Hae-kang.

77
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:20,260
Okay, Hae-kang.

78
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:33,063
Sorry.

79
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:34,022
Just eat.

80
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:37,109
No. I made a promise to myself.

81
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:38,443
He said he's on a diet.

82
00:04:38,444 --> 00:04:40,404
Something called
"intermittent fasting," sir.

83
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:41,406
I mean, Hae-kang.

84
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:43,574
Intermittent what?

85
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,034
Intermittent fasting.

86
00:04:46,035 --> 00:04:49,663
I fast for 16 hours a day

87
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:52,624
and eat freely in the remaining hours.

88
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,751
But it's fasting time right now.

89
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:56,461
Then why are you adding salt and pepper?

90
00:04:56,462 --> 00:04:57,797
I just want the feel of it.

91
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,466
Let's be an intermittent family.

92
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:02,718
Whenever it's necessary,

93
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:05,471
we'll be a mom, dad, child,
uncle, and nephew for each other.

94
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,889
And let's call this project

95
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:10,560
the "Intermittent Family Project."

96
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:15,523
Thanks to me!

97
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:18,150
What a great idea.

98
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:19,401
Intermittent family?

99
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:20,944
- That's perfect. Stop that.
- Clap.

100
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:22,363
Give him a round of applause.

101
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:27,744
Sit down. Father!

102
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:30,287
How did you come up with that?

103
00:05:30,288 --> 00:05:31,664
- Are you okay?
- Cheers to that!

104
00:05:32,373 --> 00:05:37,045
THE APARTMENT JOB

105
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:49,097
I'm just handing in the form today.

106
00:05:49,098 --> 00:05:51,308
You can come to our house
starting tomorrow.

107
00:05:51,309 --> 00:05:52,810
What form?

108
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:55,521
Wait! Stop!

109
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,983
True Value State? Your house is here?

110
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:01,194
Is there a problem?

111
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,196
Why didn't you tell me
your place was True Value?

112
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:05,323
Then I would've refused.

113
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:09,117
Why? Does someone you know live here?

114
00:06:09,118 --> 00:06:10,578
My sis…

115
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,707
Anyway, I can't do this.

116
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,587
Is this why you wanted
that penalty clause removed?

117
00:06:31,974 --> 00:06:33,601
Please pick up.

118
00:06:35,269 --> 00:06:38,147
Hey, Ha-jeong. Where are you?

119
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:42,442
I just enrolled in classes.

120
00:06:42,443 --> 00:06:44,112
- Why?
<i>- It's nothing.</i>

121
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:46,822
So you're not at work today?

122
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:48,991
Work? I took the day off.

123
00:06:50,535 --> 00:06:51,911
Still not done?

124
00:06:52,995 --> 00:06:55,498
It's nothing. See you later.

125
00:06:56,999 --> 00:06:58,543
Thank you.

126
00:07:06,634 --> 00:07:08,136
How may I help you?

127
00:07:09,887 --> 00:07:13,181
You're the one who took care of that guy
blocking the parking lot.

128
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:16,017
Things were so hectic then,
I didn't get to greet you properly.

129
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:18,187
I'm Choi Yeong-jae, the facility manager.

130
00:07:20,064 --> 00:07:21,481
I'm Park Hae-kang.

131
00:07:21,482 --> 00:07:22,400
Nice to meet you.

132
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,278
How is the parking situation?

133
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:29,740
He parks perfectly within the lines now.

134
00:07:30,366 --> 00:07:31,284
That's great.

135
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:34,828
Hey, why are we even here?

136
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:37,665
Ms. Kang,
it's intermittent family time right now.

137
00:07:38,332 --> 00:07:39,375
Ha-ri.

138
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:43,211
Mr. Kim, why are we here?

139
00:07:43,212 --> 00:07:46,298
We're here to submit
the building rep application form,

140
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,966
Ms. Kang.

141
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:49,217
Building rep?

142
00:07:49,218 --> 00:07:51,679
This is my building representative
application form.

143
00:07:53,514 --> 00:07:54,724
You're running for building rep?

144
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,436
Your photo looks great.

145
00:07:59,061 --> 00:08:00,562
Yun-seo, register this.

146
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:01,897
Yes, sir.

147
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:03,608
Who are the other…

148
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:06,277
This is my family.

149
00:08:08,362 --> 00:08:09,739
Hello.

150
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,535
My goodness.

151
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:18,289
You seem like a very close-knit family.

152
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:22,709
You could've just applied online,

153
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,796
but you brought your entire family along.
That's quite rare.

154
00:08:26,547 --> 00:08:30,593
That's right. It's rare to see
such a close-knit family these days.

155
00:08:32,428 --> 00:08:33,387
This is my wife.

156
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,223
Isn't she beautiful?

157
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,058
And my son is very bright.

158
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:40,810
He's a great son too.

159
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,853
Nice to meet you.

160
00:08:41,854 --> 00:08:44,565
And my father here used to be an artist.

161
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:48,109
These three are my younger brothers.

162
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,237
- Hello!
- Hello!

163
00:08:50,321 --> 00:08:52,281
We're a very happy family.

164
00:08:53,491 --> 00:08:54,992
Stay healthy, Father!

165
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:57,537
A very close-knit family!

166
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:00,956
- Very close brothers!
- Very close brothers!

167
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:03,416
Then is my building rep
candidate registration

168
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:05,043
complete now?

169
00:09:05,044 --> 00:09:06,127
Yes.

170
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:11,133
It'll be officially announced
in District 4 tomorrow morning.

171
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:13,427
District 4.

172
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,222
We'll do our best!

173
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:21,142
Why do I have to pay
20,000 won every month

174
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:23,353
for a gym that I never even use?

175
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,646
This is ridiculous.

176
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:26,231
- Hello.
- Hello.

177
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,692
Hello.

178
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:30,777
Mr. Choi!

179
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:33,029
Mr. Choi, come out here!

180
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,864
Hello, ma'am.

181
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:36,284
What brings you here today?

182
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:39,995
Mr. Choi, I told you last time

183
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:42,247
that I don't use the gym, sauna,

184
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,541
and breakfast services here.

185
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:47,168
Why should I pay 20,000 won
every month for them?

186
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:49,045
That's nonsense.

187
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:51,923
And I told you last time
that the 20,000 won

188
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:55,385
is a shared maintenance cost
for those services and facilities,

189
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:58,513
so every household in this complex
is required to pay it.

190
00:09:58,514 --> 00:10:00,599
Why should people who never use them

191
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,728
pay the same amount
as people who use them 30 times a month?

192
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:08,356
You can ask anyone passing by
if that makes any sense.

193
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:10,985
Don't you agree? Am I wrong?

194
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:13,029
Goodness.

195
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:15,196
- Pardon?
- You're the guy

196
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:18,700
who hit that car
in front of the parking lot last time.

197
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:19,910
Hello.

198
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:21,454
Right.

199
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,667
I'm Park Hae-kang.

200
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:29,044
I'm Jang Suk-jin.

201
00:10:29,045 --> 00:10:30,463
Seeing you up close,

202
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:32,882
you're quite handsome.

203
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:36,551
He's my eldest son.

204
00:10:36,552 --> 00:10:39,220
But what brings you here?

205
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:41,931
Why would you ask him that?

206
00:10:41,932 --> 00:10:45,894
I should know everything going on
in my apartment complex.

207
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,771
I need to be aware of everything.

208
00:10:47,772 --> 00:10:49,814
What are they doing here?

209
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:51,983
He's running for building representative.

210
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:53,235
Really?

211
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:55,321
Building representative?

212
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:58,658
I see.

213
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,618
And these folks are…

214
00:11:02,286 --> 00:11:04,372
This is my close-knit family.

215
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:06,665
- Hello, ma'am.
- Hello, ma'am.

216
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:08,376
Bonjour, charming lady.

217
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:10,378
Your family?

218
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:12,963
Goodness me.

219
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:20,470
There's no way I'd forget people
who stand out this much.

220
00:11:20,471 --> 00:11:22,847
So you all

221
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,974
are actually a family?

222
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:26,185
Ma'am.

223
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,395
They just said they're a family.

224
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:30,605
Why would they lie about being a family?

225
00:11:30,606 --> 00:11:31,607
I just meant…

226
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:36,778
I'm the eyes and ears of True Value State.

227
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:40,198
But strangely,
I've never seen these people before, so--

228
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:44,078
Ms. Jang, if your business here is done,
why don't you leave…

229
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:49,083
Right. How strange.

230
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:50,875
- Strange…
- Mr. Choi.

231
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:53,254
- Yes?
- Did you check?

232
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,130
Check what?

233
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:57,340
You know,

234
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,300
my application
for building representative.

235
00:11:59,301 --> 00:12:02,388
I applied online ages ago.

236
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:07,350
Right, everyone.

237
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:11,187
Let's all make True Value
a great apartment complex.

238
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:13,064
Let's all try our best.

239
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:14,107
Let's do this together.

240
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:16,110
Right. Let's do this together.

241
00:12:19,196 --> 00:12:20,448
Just a little more.

242
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:22,783
You can be like Hae-kang. Just a bit more.

243
00:12:23,659 --> 00:12:26,077
Almost there. Yes.

244
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,162
Let me ask one thing.

245
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:29,081
Why are you trying to be a building rep?

246
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,667
I won't stop there.

247
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,251
What?

248
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:34,295
I'm going to be

249
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,465
the residents' association president.

250
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:40,551
But why?

251
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:42,386
I'm a great leader.

252
00:12:44,346 --> 00:12:45,598
A leader?

253
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:49,559
Don't ignore my sincerity
for making our complex--

254
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,270
Don't say anything.
It'll be something shady anyway.

255
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:55,816
All I care about is getting my money,
so don't tell me anything.

256
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:59,069
This won't harm you in any way.

257
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:02,363
If I become the president,
I'll give you a bonus--

258
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:03,531
Mr. Park.

259
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:05,784
Make sure to succeed.

260
00:13:07,661 --> 00:13:10,247
I'm going home now. It's six.

261
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:16,712
Ms. Kang!

262
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:19,547
Get home safely.

263
00:13:19,548 --> 00:13:21,342
- Here.
- It's fine.

264
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:23,343
See you tomorrow.

265
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:26,096
Get home safe, Ha-ri.

266
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:30,809
Why did it have to be True Value
of all places?

267
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:35,022
Ha-jeong will kill me if she finds out.

268
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,194
FRENCH PASTRIES BY LE CORDE D'OR GRADUATE

269
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,955
Kang Ha-jeong.

270
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:53,332
Go to France.

271
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,833
What? Why would I go there?

272
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,835
When it comes to bread,
it has to be France.

273
00:13:57,836 --> 00:14:00,673
Go and experience the food yourself
and travel a bit.

274
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:03,926
- Are you crazy? We don't have the money.
- I'm…

275
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:06,303
a lawyer, remember?

276
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:11,057
I can't. I have to work.

277
00:14:11,058 --> 00:14:14,394
You're not the only employee there.
You have vacation days left.

278
00:14:14,395 --> 00:14:15,854
Right, but…

279
00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:19,400
There's the building rep
and president election.

280
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:23,195
This is your only chance, Ha-jeong.

281
00:14:23,862 --> 00:14:25,656
Well, I'll ask.

282
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:28,242
But I'm not sure they'll let me.

283
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:30,911
Just talk to them.

284
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:35,707
Yes?

285
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:38,210
<i>Mr. Park, are you working
on getting the ten billion?</i>

286
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:40,588
Three months.

287
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:43,257
I just need three months.

288
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:48,344
I know you can do it, Mr. Park.

289
00:14:48,345 --> 00:14:49,971
<i>I believe in you.</i>

290
00:14:49,972 --> 00:14:52,224
Then keep your promise
about returning everything

291
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:54,935
back to normal.

292
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:56,729
Just bring the money.

293
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:08,407
I'm the designated driver.

294
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:16,165
I'm the designated driver you called for.

295
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:18,083
This way, sir.

296
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:23,588
I told you, didn't I?

297
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:25,549
Park Hae-kang can pull off anything.

298
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:27,176
Yes. Three months.

299
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,470
He'll get it within three months.

300
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:33,766
It's nothing.

301
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:36,769
All I did was make a few calls.

302
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:41,774
KIM GYEONG-NAM

303
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:44,609
- Yes?
<i>- Boss.</i>

304
00:15:44,610 --> 00:15:48,238
It seems the Chief really is taking orders
from someone else.

305
00:15:48,822 --> 00:15:50,531
I'll keep tailing him.

306
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:52,617
Be careful not to get caught.

307
00:15:52,618 --> 00:15:53,452
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

308
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:09,093
The president is here.

309
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:11,887
It's the president.

310
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:17,183
Everyone is here.

311
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:18,851
I hope everything is going well.

312
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,436
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

313
00:16:20,437 --> 00:16:21,604
Can you hear me clearly?

314
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:23,106
- Yes.
- Yes, sir.

315
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,691
Then I'll talk without the mic.

316
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:26,944
This feels awkward for me.

317
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,780
I've gathered sole candidates
from each district,

318
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:33,324
including District 1, where I'm running.

319
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:36,703
Since you're the sole candidates,

320
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:40,832
you'll be elected
as the representative anyway.

321
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,834
It's quite troubling

322
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:45,920
how uninterested the residents are
in our complex's affairs.

323
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:47,380
Everyone's busy making a living.

324
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:49,173
We should be understanding.

325
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:53,177
But if we're sole candidates,
do we even need an election?

326
00:16:53,178 --> 00:16:54,971
That's what I mean.

327
00:16:54,972 --> 00:16:57,223
It takes money, time, and resources

328
00:16:57,224 --> 00:16:59,268
- for the election.
- Right.

329
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:03,772
Well, there are election regulations,
so we have to follow them.

330
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:07,650
We should uphold basic principles

331
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:11,279
right here where we live.

332
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,573
That's how basic principles

333
00:17:13,574 --> 00:17:16,868
will be upheld in our society,
and ultimately in Korea.

334
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:21,373
That's what I've always
thought and believed.

335
00:17:21,957 --> 00:17:23,125
A round of applause.

336
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:29,380
Our president really has a way with words.

337
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:31,966
You'll be the president again, won't you?

338
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:32,885
You should.

339
00:17:34,762 --> 00:17:36,137
Well…

340
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:38,264
As some of you may know,

341
00:17:38,265 --> 00:17:42,060
I'm not someone
who's attached to positions.

342
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:43,728
What do you mean?

343
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,440
Who else besides you
would be our association's president?

344
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:53,905
But I don't see the candidates
from Districts 4 and 6.

345
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:56,115
The one from District 6 is…

346
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:57,326
I

347
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,495
didn't invite her.

348
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,206
She's a young mother,

349
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:05,709
but you know how young mothers are.

350
00:18:06,543 --> 00:18:09,505
They're all talk and no substance.

351
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:14,926
I just can't stand noisy people.

352
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:17,136
And as for District 4,

353
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:19,223
the situation there is a bit different.

354
00:18:23,894 --> 00:18:25,896
- This is fun!
- Stop running, Gyeong-buk.

355
00:18:29,608 --> 00:18:30,733
Gyeong-buk!

356
00:18:30,734 --> 00:18:31,943
I told you not to run.

357
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:33,903
This isn't Grandma's house.

358
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:37,491
The downstairs neighbors will complain.
They have students who need to study.

359
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:42,996
What's with this color?

360
00:18:43,705 --> 00:18:45,748
Pink is the perfect color for a man.

361
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:48,042
What's your candidate number?
I didn't know it,

362
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:49,794
so I just got your name printed.

363
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,796
He's the sole candidate.
There's no number.

364
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:54,924
Boss, the campaign truck
will arrive at 11 a.m.

365
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:56,717
We've prepared the loudest speakers,

366
00:18:56,718 --> 00:18:59,220
so you just have to show up
and hand out business cards.

367
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,388
Your gloves.

368
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:03,266
Uncle Hae-kang has to shake hands
with everyone, so there's no need.

369
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,059
I'll give them to the others.

370
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:08,062
I was a facility manager for years.

371
00:19:08,063 --> 00:19:11,482
I'm telling you
a campaign for building rep is excessive.

372
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:13,484
Are you running for office or what?

373
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:15,737
- Who the hell would go this far?
- Gyeong-buk.

374
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:19,825
If he doesn't win the election,
you're dead.

375
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:22,286
There's a kid here. Watch your words.

376
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:24,871
Did the rooftop not scare you enough?

377
00:19:24,872 --> 00:19:26,081
Read the room.

378
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:30,544
He's the sole candidate.
There's no need for business cards.

379
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,462
He doesn't have to do anything…

380
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,048
Oh, Ms. Kang must be here.

381
00:19:37,134 --> 00:19:39,136
Stop stomping around like that!

382
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,516
<i>Everyone, come out here.</i>

383
00:19:45,601 --> 00:19:47,268
FINAL LIST OF BUILDING REP CANDIDATES

384
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:48,103
CANDIDATE PROFILE

385
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:57,862
Was having three candidates
part of your perfect plan?

386
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,113
What do we do, Boss?

387
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:00,406
There are too many candidates.

388
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:03,117
And she's that woman we saw yesterday.

389
00:20:03,118 --> 00:20:04,745
She was your rival.

390
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:09,249
You said no one's interested.

391
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,294
Why are there
so many passionate people here?

392
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:15,255
There's nothing to gain from this.

393
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:32,064
"I'll be a diligent worker
for True Value."

394
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:34,775
What do you think, Mr. Kim?

395
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:36,984
Pardon?

396
00:20:36,985 --> 00:20:39,153
Do you think Park Hae-kang

397
00:20:39,154 --> 00:20:41,949
can be a diligent worker for True Value?

398
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:43,533
I'm not sure.

399
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:56,922
I spent a fortune on the landscaping here.

400
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,801
I said I'd carry it.

401
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,178
You can take it from here.

402
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:08,349
I told you,

403
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:11,310
you shouldn't have booked tickets
without even asking me.

404
00:21:11,311 --> 00:21:15,856
I have no choice but to go
since we can't get a refund, but…

405
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:17,441
Don't worry.

406
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:18,776
Just go and experience

407
00:21:18,777 --> 00:21:20,904
every kind of bread there is,
starting with baguettes.

408
00:21:21,822 --> 00:21:24,783
I can't believe you did this for me.

409
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:27,828
You have your passport, don't you? Go.

410
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:31,206
Thank you, Ha-ri.

411
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,040
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

412
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:36,295
<i>But what excuse will I use to stop her
from coming to work in two weeks?</i>

413
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:38,337
I'll really get going now.

414
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:39,798
- Thank you.
- Go on.

415
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,637
Please…

416
00:21:46,263 --> 00:21:47,930
I won't mind a foreign brother-in-law,

417
00:21:47,931 --> 00:21:50,725
so can't you meet someone there
and just keep living there?

418
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:52,643
Bye.

419
00:21:52,644 --> 00:21:53,603
Take care!

420
00:22:02,154 --> 00:22:06,032
I'm Candidate 3 for District 4,

421
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:07,826
Park Hae-kang!

422
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:10,911
I'll do my best!

423
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:13,957
I'm your diligent worker,
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

424
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:16,917
TRUE VALUE'S DILIGENT WORKER
PARK HAE-KANG

425
00:22:16,918 --> 00:22:18,086
Park Hae-kang!

426
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:21,923
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

427
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:25,384
Hello!

428
00:22:25,385 --> 00:22:27,053
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

429
00:22:27,054 --> 00:22:29,765
Nice to meet you.
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

430
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:34,061
Candidate 3.

431
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:36,437
We're getting so many complaints.

432
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:38,065
They said they'll call the police.

433
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,107
This is new.

434
00:22:40,108 --> 00:22:41,276
I'll do my best!

435
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:44,987
District 4, building representative

436
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:47,281
- Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!
- True Value, Park Hae-kang!

437
00:22:47,282 --> 00:22:49,241
True Value, Park Hae-kang!

438
00:22:49,242 --> 00:22:50,326
Ms. Kang!

439
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:52,661
- Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!
- Ms. Kang!

440
00:22:52,662 --> 00:22:55,331
Ms. Kang! Jump!

441
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:56,833
- I'll do my best!
- Jump!

442
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:04,341
We can't campaign anymore.
What do we do now?

443
00:23:05,258 --> 00:23:07,094
Are you going to keep
pacing around like that?

444
00:23:07,636 --> 00:23:12,306
This is the perfect time for him
to finish thinking

445
00:23:12,307 --> 00:23:16,019
and come up with an amazing idea…

446
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,569
Move aside. Let me see.

447
00:23:26,947 --> 00:23:29,658
Candidate 2, Shin Bong-su.
His campaign pledge is…

448
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:32,410
"I'll create a designated smoking area."

449
00:23:33,286 --> 00:23:36,455
But isn't this a non-smoking
apartment complex?

450
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:38,374
There are children everywhere.

451
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:40,960
The mothers won't just let him
make a smoking area.

452
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:42,212
They won't vote for him. He's out.

453
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:45,548
Next, Candidate 1. Jang Suk-jin.

454
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:47,758
"I'll have Exit 3
of Line 10's Oman Station

455
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:50,010
relocated to the front
of True Value State."

456
00:23:50,011 --> 00:23:53,097
How would she relocate a subway exit?

457
00:23:53,098 --> 00:23:54,723
Is this even feasible?

458
00:23:54,724 --> 00:23:57,518
A proposal to connect the station
to True Value was turned down,

459
00:23:57,519 --> 00:24:00,604
but some residents still haven't
given up hope and are protesting.

460
00:24:00,605 --> 00:24:02,649
- That's what we call--
- The PIMFY phenomenon.

461
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:04,984
How could she do something

462
00:24:04,985 --> 00:24:07,153
even a National Assembly member can't?

463
00:24:07,154 --> 00:24:08,405
She won't win either.

464
00:24:09,489 --> 00:24:11,824
Next, Candidate 3. Park Hae-kang.

465
00:24:11,825 --> 00:24:14,452
"I'll be a diligent worker
for True Value."

466
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:17,372
How exactly do you plan on doing that?

467
00:24:25,380 --> 00:24:26,422
We'll get to that--

468
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:27,882
See?

469
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:30,301
How will you defeat the others
with such complacency?

470
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:32,678
With that suit, that tone,
and that messy hair…

471
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:35,140
Do you even want
to become the building rep?

472
00:24:40,478 --> 00:24:42,564
Put your phone on silent during meetings.

473
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:44,399
Hello?

474
00:24:46,109 --> 00:24:47,402
What do you mean?

475
00:24:48,153 --> 00:24:49,487
Pick up our packages?

476
00:24:53,116 --> 00:24:56,452
You can't just leave
all the packages here!

477
00:24:56,453 --> 00:24:58,329
You're supposed to deliver them!

478
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:01,999
We can't even if we want to.
They won't let our trucks enter!

479
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,002
We want our packages delivered
conveniently to our doorstep.

480
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:07,213
We didn't pay to carry them ourselves.

481
00:25:07,214 --> 00:25:08,756
Don't take it out on us.

482
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:10,966
Tell that to the people
who won't let us enter.

483
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:13,344
Then you should carry them
to our houses yourselves!

484
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:15,095
You took our delivery fees, damn it!

485
00:25:15,096 --> 00:25:16,889
You should finish your job!

486
00:25:16,890 --> 00:25:19,392
What? "Damn it"?

487
00:25:22,103 --> 00:25:23,480
You deliver them yourselves.

488
00:25:24,105 --> 00:25:27,024
- You're always making a huge fuss.
- Sir…

489
00:25:27,025 --> 00:25:29,694
This is a delivery crisis.

490
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:34,698
The trucks make mothers worried
about their kids' safety,

491
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:37,117
ruin the landscaping,
and pump out exhaust fumes.

492
00:25:37,118 --> 00:25:39,995
So they want them to use
the underground parking lot,

493
00:25:39,996 --> 00:25:41,872
but on the other hand,

494
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:44,458
look at the trucks. They're huge.

495
00:25:44,459 --> 00:25:46,585
They can't enter the parking lot.

496
00:25:46,586 --> 00:25:48,504
They'll have to modify the trucks,

497
00:25:48,505 --> 00:25:52,175
but that would cost money.
That's why this is happening.

498
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:56,553
I do understand both sides.
It's a difficult situation.

499
00:25:56,554 --> 00:25:58,347
Let's go get our packages.

500
00:25:58,348 --> 00:25:59,808
- Yeah.
- Okay.

501
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:01,184
Father.

502
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:12,528
Are you all right?

503
00:26:12,529 --> 00:26:14,905
Where do you live?
I'll carry that for you.

504
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:16,532
I live in Building 107.

505
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:17,450
All right.

506
00:26:38,179 --> 00:26:39,638
This is your chance.

507
00:26:39,639 --> 00:26:40,764
What chance?

508
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:43,393
Your chance to be a diligent worker
for True Value.

509
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,479
Look at this mess.

510
00:26:52,944 --> 00:26:54,154
You can't…

511
00:26:59,492 --> 00:27:01,036
I'll take care of this problem!

512
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:06,833
True Value's diligent worker.

513
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:10,045
I'm Candidate 3 of District 4,

514
00:27:12,047 --> 00:27:13,298
Park Hae-kang.

515
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:23,141
WIN-WIN

516
00:27:30,190 --> 00:27:31,524
Hello.

517
00:27:32,776 --> 00:27:34,276
District 4's building representative

518
00:27:34,277 --> 00:27:36,236
Candidate 3,

519
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:38,364
True Value's diligent worker,
Park Hae-kang.

520
00:27:38,365 --> 00:27:39,865
I've done my best

521
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:44,788
to find a win-win solution between
True Value and the delivery companies.

522
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:51,001
<i>To prevent package loss,</i>

523
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:53,295
<i>deliveries will be sorted by building</i>

524
00:27:53,296 --> 00:27:56,883
<i>and handed over directly
after verifying the recipient.</i>

525
00:27:57,967 --> 00:27:59,009
Here you go.

526
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:00,260
<i>One more thing.</i>

527
00:28:00,261 --> 00:28:03,430
<i>If you tell our partners
your building and unit number,</i>

528
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:05,432
<i>we'll deliver them</i>

529
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:06,810
to your doorstep!

530
00:28:16,736 --> 00:28:17,862
Je-gil!

531
00:28:21,658 --> 00:28:23,243
Delivery!

532
00:28:23,868 --> 00:28:25,370
- Hello. Thank you.
- Here you go.

533
00:28:26,329 --> 00:28:27,372
Wait!

534
00:28:27,956 --> 00:28:28,873
Thank you.

535
00:28:30,041 --> 00:28:30,999
This was delicious.

536
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,710
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

537
00:28:34,462 --> 00:28:36,130
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

538
00:28:36,131 --> 00:28:37,757
- Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.
- Yes.

539
00:28:38,341 --> 00:28:39,883
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

540
00:28:39,884 --> 00:28:42,052
You wouldn't have been able
to carry this here.

541
00:28:42,053 --> 00:28:43,763
- I'm glad we helped out.
- Thank you.

542
00:28:48,643 --> 00:28:50,103
- Wait!
- Over here.

543
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:53,897
I made some kimchi pancake.

544
00:28:53,898 --> 00:28:55,441
We've been waiting for you. Try this.

545
00:28:55,442 --> 00:28:56,817
Try this too.

546
00:28:56,818 --> 00:28:57,901
Thank you, ladies.

547
00:28:57,902 --> 00:29:00,738
Vote for Candidate Number 3!

548
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,614
You're the best! Visit us again!

549
00:29:02,615 --> 00:29:04,450
Vote for Candidate Number 3!

550
00:29:04,451 --> 00:29:05,701
Unit 1306!

551
00:29:05,702 --> 00:29:07,411
Next time! I'm busy!

552
00:29:07,412 --> 00:29:08,788
When will you be back?

553
00:29:11,332 --> 00:29:13,167
Delivery!

554
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:15,627
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

555
00:29:15,628 --> 00:29:16,921
Keep up the good work!

556
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:19,506
That's a lot of candidates.

557
00:29:19,507 --> 00:29:21,133
Yeah.

558
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:23,343
But if I were in District 4,

559
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:25,512
- I'd want to pick Candidate 3.
- Right?

560
00:29:25,513 --> 00:29:27,931
I should tell Min-ji's mom
to vote for him.

561
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:28,849
You should.

562
00:29:28,850 --> 00:29:30,893
It's not easy delivering packages.

563
00:29:30,894 --> 00:29:33,645
Why'd the residents' association
stop the trucks from entering?

564
00:29:33,646 --> 00:29:35,439
- It's such a pain.
- Right?

565
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:37,859
Hello.

566
00:29:38,902 --> 00:29:40,569
You're from Building 108, aren't you?

567
00:29:40,570 --> 00:29:41,779
- Yes.
- Yes.

568
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:44,573
But we all have hands, you know.

569
00:29:44,574 --> 00:29:46,909
Everyone can just
take their own packages home.

570
00:29:46,910 --> 00:29:48,660
How long will they keep this up?

571
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:51,456
It's not like they'll keep
delivering packages for us forever.

572
00:29:52,165 --> 00:29:55,918
This is what we call vote-buying promises.

573
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:57,921
You should know that.

574
00:29:58,713 --> 00:30:01,882
Pay attention to the other candidates too.

575
00:30:01,883 --> 00:30:02,841
- Right.
- Sure.

576
00:30:02,842 --> 00:30:04,676
Please show some interest!

577
00:30:04,677 --> 00:30:07,055
Reject Oman Station Exit 3.

578
00:30:09,599 --> 00:30:11,391
- I'm here.
- Welcome.

579
00:30:11,392 --> 00:30:12,685
- Hi.
- Hi.

580
00:30:14,270 --> 00:30:16,146
Wow, this is your breakfast?

581
00:30:16,147 --> 00:30:17,606
You even have grilled hairtail.

582
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:19,608
You haven't had breakfast,
have you, Ms. Kang?

583
00:30:19,609 --> 00:30:21,236
Sit wherever you'd like.

584
00:30:22,570 --> 00:30:25,781
This seat is comfy.

585
00:30:25,782 --> 00:30:27,533
What is it? What?

586
00:30:27,534 --> 00:30:29,159
Mom, sit next to me.

587
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:30,078
Over here.

588
00:30:30,787 --> 00:30:31,621
Sure.

589
00:30:35,416 --> 00:30:36,584
Have some.

590
00:30:39,712 --> 00:30:41,672
It's a mountain of rice.

591
00:30:41,673 --> 00:30:43,715
Let me know if that's not enough.

592
00:30:43,716 --> 00:30:45,468
- Not enough?
- Just in case.

593
00:30:50,431 --> 00:30:52,766
- Have some bulgogi.
- It's fine.

594
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:54,978
It's really tasty. It melts in your mouth.

595
00:30:57,730 --> 00:30:58,815
Unbelievable.

596
00:30:59,482 --> 00:31:01,441
Aren't you eating, Mr. Park?

597
00:31:01,442 --> 00:31:03,820
This is enough for me.

598
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:05,779
Espresso?

599
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:07,615
You're no fun at all.

600
00:31:17,458 --> 00:31:18,334
Hey, kid.

601
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:21,420
What was your name again? Gyeong-nam?

602
00:31:21,421 --> 00:31:23,088
- What?
- What?

603
00:31:23,089 --> 00:31:24,007
That's me.

604
00:31:24,674 --> 00:31:25,799
Right.

605
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,217
Mom.

606
00:31:27,218 --> 00:31:29,303
I'm Gyeong-buk.

607
00:31:29,304 --> 00:31:30,430
Kim Gyeong-buk.

608
00:31:31,556 --> 00:31:32,974
Right. Kim Gyeong-buk.

609
00:31:33,474 --> 00:31:34,559
Look.

610
00:31:43,735 --> 00:31:45,361
Do it like this.

611
00:31:47,614 --> 00:31:48,739
- Okay?
- Yes.

612
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:50,700
This is how you debone hairtail.

613
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,910
You're the best, Mom.

614
00:31:52,911 --> 00:31:54,579
You're like a hairtail genius.

615
00:31:55,872 --> 00:31:56,748
That's enough.

616
00:31:57,248 --> 00:32:00,042
You shouldn't be moved
by something so trivial.

617
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,503
I'm allergic to failure, you know.

618
00:32:03,630 --> 00:32:06,841
So I can't stand seeing people failing.

619
00:32:41,584 --> 00:32:44,628
Can't you see
I'm focused right now, Mr. Kim?

620
00:32:44,629 --> 00:32:47,256
There's something you need to see, sir.

621
00:32:47,882 --> 00:32:48,924
<i>Breaking news.</i>

622
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:53,011
<i>The candidate sites for the fourth
new town have just been announced.</i>

623
00:32:53,012 --> 00:32:55,222
<i>Sihyeon District of Gwangmyeong,
Gyeonggi Province,</i>

624
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:56,765
<i>Yusu District of Seongnam,</i>

625
00:32:56,766 --> 00:33:00,102
<i>and the Hanju area
and Suyeong-dong of Incheon</i>

626
00:33:00,103 --> 00:33:02,354
<i>have been chosen as the candidates.</i>

627
00:33:02,355 --> 00:33:04,439
<i>The selection was based
on the evaluation criteria</i>

628
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:06,608
<i>of the Ministry of Land,
Infrastructure, and Transport…</i>

629
00:33:06,609 --> 00:33:07,610
Oh dear.

630
00:33:08,319 --> 00:33:09,737
Oman wasn't included.

631
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:13,241
Apparently, it wasn't even mentioned.

632
00:33:13,741 --> 00:33:15,326
Really?

633
00:33:17,453 --> 00:33:19,205
That's pretty upsetting.

634
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:22,875
Why don't we go fishing
to lighten our mood?

635
00:33:24,210 --> 00:33:26,003
Right now, sir?

636
00:33:26,004 --> 00:33:30,173
Yes. I really want
to go fishing right now.

637
00:33:30,174 --> 00:33:33,385
But it would be too intimate
and gross for us to go alone.

638
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:35,263
Let's take the elders with us.

639
00:33:36,973 --> 00:33:38,349
I'll make the preparations.

640
00:33:39,350 --> 00:33:40,309
You do that.

641
00:33:48,067 --> 00:33:50,652
I should prepare some saw-edged perch

642
00:33:50,653 --> 00:33:51,904
for the elders to eat.

643
00:34:28,816 --> 00:34:31,151
MINISTER OF LAND, INFRASTRUCTURE,
AND TRANSPORT, KIM JONG-SIK

644
00:34:31,152 --> 00:34:32,945
The fish just aren't biting today.

645
00:34:34,197 --> 00:34:35,113
Seriously.

646
00:34:35,114 --> 00:34:37,699
NATIONAL ASSEMBLY MEMBER
JANG AN-SU

647
00:34:37,700 --> 00:34:40,328
MAYOR OF OMAN CITY
HAN MUN-HO

648
00:34:40,995 --> 00:34:43,371
Let's head back now, Mr. Lee.

649
00:34:43,372 --> 00:34:45,541
But we've spent so much time here.

650
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,794
We can't head back empty-handed.

651
00:34:49,754 --> 00:34:52,256
I am getting kind of hungry, though.

652
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:55,301
Hey.

653
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:58,012
- Bring that here.
- Right. Bring it here!

654
00:35:02,391 --> 00:35:03,308
Ta-da.

655
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:05,435
I thought something like this
might happen,

656
00:35:05,436 --> 00:35:09,607
so I got some wild-caught saw-edged perch
from Jeju Island myself.

657
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:12,443
You're so prepared.

658
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:14,695
Mayor, here you go.

659
00:35:15,863 --> 00:35:16,906
Open up.

660
00:35:18,407 --> 00:35:20,325
This is embarrassing.

661
00:35:20,326 --> 00:35:22,285
Sir, please. Just once.

662
00:35:22,286 --> 00:35:23,496
Open up.

663
00:35:24,664 --> 00:35:25,915
All right.

664
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:30,294
That's right. Very good.

665
00:35:32,505 --> 00:35:33,422
Wait, what…

666
00:35:35,007 --> 00:35:37,426
Open his mouth wider.

667
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:41,347
Sir, let me give you some
red pepper paste.

668
00:35:47,019 --> 00:35:48,687
Mr. Lee!

669
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:51,148
What the hell are you doing?

670
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,024
Have you lost it?

671
00:35:52,733 --> 00:35:55,570
You can't even do your job,
you can't catch any fish,

672
00:35:56,362 --> 00:35:58,363
but you still want some saw-edged perch.

673
00:35:58,364 --> 00:36:01,075
Don't you think that would irritate me?

674
00:36:01,742 --> 00:36:03,995
You really are clueless.

675
00:36:04,745 --> 00:36:07,122
You took my money

676
00:36:07,123 --> 00:36:08,915
but blew the new town deal.

677
00:36:08,916 --> 00:36:11,334
Did you really think I'd rent a boat

678
00:36:11,335 --> 00:36:14,338
and prepare all this for you
out of gratitude?

679
00:36:14,964 --> 00:36:16,506
Mr. Lee,

680
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:19,593
sometimes,
we need to let go of the small things

681
00:36:19,594 --> 00:36:20,887
for the bigger picture…

682
00:36:23,973 --> 00:36:25,183
What bigger picture?

683
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:29,395
Do you know what Won Bin
said in that movie?

684
00:36:33,149 --> 00:36:35,318
"You only live for tomorrow, don't you?"

685
00:36:36,402 --> 00:36:38,362
"I only live for today."

686
00:36:38,946 --> 00:36:42,241
"And you won't survive
against a guy who lives only for today."

687
00:36:47,914 --> 00:36:51,459
I'm someone who only lives for today,
so if anyone pisses me off,

688
00:36:52,168 --> 00:36:55,045
I have to take it out on them right away.

689
00:36:55,046 --> 00:36:56,005
Minister.

690
00:36:56,923 --> 00:36:58,716
Why don't you take a dip?

691
00:37:06,015 --> 00:37:08,475
Let's talk this out!

692
00:37:08,476 --> 00:37:12,729
I'll do my best to get
the new town project approved!

693
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:14,106
I swear!

694
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,860
I can't swim!

695
00:37:19,362 --> 00:37:23,074
Mr. Lee! Help me!

696
00:37:24,116 --> 00:37:26,701
I'll return everything you gave me.

697
00:37:26,702 --> 00:37:31,081
I'm sorry, but Oman was ruled out
due to the regulations.

698
00:37:31,082 --> 00:37:34,417
That was because
you didn't do your job properly.

699
00:37:34,418 --> 00:37:36,753
If I gave you bullets
to get them on our side, then…

700
00:37:36,754 --> 00:37:38,130
Bang, bang!

701
00:37:39,632 --> 00:37:41,259
You should've shot them.

702
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:43,886
But you just took them all for yourself.

703
00:37:45,179 --> 00:37:46,597
How did you think this would play out?

704
00:37:48,015 --> 00:37:51,394
You need a good scolding today.

705
00:37:54,230 --> 00:37:55,438
What are you doing?

706
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:56,899
Mr. Lee!

707
00:38:00,486 --> 00:38:01,362
We'll…

708
00:38:02,029 --> 00:38:04,531
We'll take care of this.

709
00:38:04,532 --> 00:38:05,865
Will you?

710
00:38:05,866 --> 00:38:07,034
Of course.

711
00:38:07,660 --> 00:38:09,494
Can I trust you?

712
00:38:09,495 --> 00:38:10,537
- Yes.
- Of course.

713
00:38:10,538 --> 00:38:12,415
If you disappoint me again,

714
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:15,084
I'll really lose my head.

715
00:38:28,472 --> 00:38:30,516
This really melts in your mouth.

716
00:38:34,228 --> 00:38:35,104
Hey.

717
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:38,023
I'm from Unit 1802.

718
00:38:38,024 --> 00:38:42,069
If there's anything broken or ruined,
you're dead.

719
00:38:43,696 --> 00:38:44,739
Be careful with it.

720
00:38:45,531 --> 00:38:47,033
- Yes, sir.
- Okay.

721
00:38:48,576 --> 00:38:49,577
Hey!

722
00:38:50,703 --> 00:38:53,580
Don't take the elevator.
Carry them up the stairs.

723
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:56,667
I hate it when delivery guys
hold up the elevator.

724
00:38:58,294 --> 00:39:00,379
What? You got a problem?

725
00:39:03,507 --> 00:39:04,842
What's with the face?

726
00:39:07,053 --> 00:39:10,013
Did something happen when you were born,
or is it your genes?

727
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:11,139
That jerk.

728
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:12,266
Did he just hit him?

729
00:39:14,101 --> 00:39:16,353
He's a voter in District 4.

730
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,104
- Boss.
- Boss.

731
00:39:18,105 --> 00:39:20,399
- How could you…
- You rude jerks.

732
00:39:37,750 --> 00:39:39,001
I'm aching all over.

733
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:41,796
I didn't even do much.
Why am I so exhausted?

734
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:43,421
Mr. Park.

735
00:39:43,422 --> 00:39:45,508
Can I have a pain relief patch too?

736
00:39:46,509 --> 00:39:47,343
Here.

737
00:39:49,345 --> 00:39:50,638
Thanks.

738
00:39:52,890 --> 00:39:55,267
I feel like I lost five kilos already.

739
00:39:55,851 --> 00:39:58,603
Can you order us some chicken?

740
00:39:58,604 --> 00:39:59,647
My legs…

741
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:07,070
Boss, the apartment complex forum
is buzzing about this.

742
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:08,030
Really?

743
00:40:08,656 --> 00:40:09,949
Let me see. Bring it here.

744
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:20,375
They're all grateful

745
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:22,502
and say that it was really helpful.

746
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:25,714
They're calling you the hero
who solved the delivery crisis.

747
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:30,885
Hang on.

748
00:40:30,886 --> 00:40:32,638
Scroll back up a bit.

749
00:40:33,848 --> 00:40:36,308
"Request to discontinue…"

750
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,269
Give me that.

751
00:40:39,478 --> 00:40:40,979
"Discontinue the delivery service?"

752
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:41,939
Why?

753
00:40:42,731 --> 00:40:43,774
What happened here?

754
00:40:45,526 --> 00:40:48,153
"All my deliveries are damaged,

755
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:50,113
and things have gone missing."

756
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:52,324
"Shouldn't we verify
the delivery workers' identities?"

757
00:40:53,159 --> 00:40:55,453
They were getting paid.
They wouldn't have done this.

758
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,544
Take a good look at this.

759
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:08,841
Tell me honestly.

760
00:41:12,761 --> 00:41:14,555
Who messed with the deliveries?

761
00:41:15,181 --> 00:41:18,600
Boss, you can chop our hands off
if we really did this.

762
00:41:18,601 --> 00:41:20,477
We're not in some gang, you know.

763
00:41:20,478 --> 00:41:23,521
I'm not chopping your hands off.
I'm docking your pay.

764
00:41:23,522 --> 00:41:25,273
- It's not us!
- We really didn't do it!

765
00:41:25,274 --> 00:41:27,609
We don't even know what's in the parcels.

766
00:41:27,610 --> 00:41:29,611
How would we mess with them?

767
00:41:29,612 --> 00:41:32,071
Then what's this anonymous post?

768
00:41:32,072 --> 00:41:34,282
The kimchi was leaking,
some apples were missing,

769
00:41:34,283 --> 00:41:37,202
and the potatoes and sweet potatoes
were all damaged.

770
00:41:37,203 --> 00:41:40,788
Boss, by any chance,
is it Unit 902 in Building 112?

771
00:41:40,789 --> 00:41:42,624
They always order heavy stuff,

772
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:44,834
so I remember the address.

773
00:41:44,835 --> 00:41:46,170
I think it is.

774
00:41:48,547 --> 00:41:50,591
The proof of delivery photos look fine.

775
00:41:53,928 --> 00:41:56,346
Boss. Unit 902 of Building 112

776
00:41:56,347 --> 00:41:59,266
is Candidate Jang's place.

777
00:42:08,108 --> 00:42:11,320
She's going negative
over a building rep election?

778
00:42:12,029 --> 00:42:13,655
Negative…

779
00:42:13,656 --> 00:42:14,740
What does that mean?

780
00:42:17,284 --> 00:42:19,245
- It's English.
- It's just a term.

781
00:42:20,246 --> 00:42:23,456
It's "negative campaigning"
when you make baseless accusations

782
00:42:23,457 --> 00:42:25,833
about your opponent during an election.

783
00:42:25,834 --> 00:42:29,045
This is all because
she's feeling threatened

784
00:42:29,046 --> 00:42:30,631
by Mr. Park pulling ahead.

785
00:42:31,423 --> 00:42:33,841
Still, how can she lie like this?

786
00:42:33,842 --> 00:42:35,843
Elections are always messy.

787
00:42:35,844 --> 00:42:37,845
That's democracy for you.

788
00:42:37,846 --> 00:42:39,180
What should we do?

789
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:41,558
It's obvious, isn't it?

790
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:43,101
Fight negative with negative.

791
00:42:43,102 --> 00:42:44,937
Negative with negative…

792
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:48,147
Let's take down

793
00:42:48,148 --> 00:42:49,607
- Jang Suk-jin.
- Yes.

794
00:42:49,608 --> 00:42:50,692
What?

795
00:42:50,693 --> 00:42:53,111
We don't need to do the same to her…

796
00:42:53,112 --> 00:42:54,738
Do you guys remember

797
00:42:55,447 --> 00:42:58,658
the day we caught the Salamander

798
00:42:58,659 --> 00:43:00,494
from Incheon's Sewer Gang?

799
00:43:42,328 --> 00:43:43,704
I missed you, Salamander.

800
00:44:12,858 --> 00:44:13,984
Watch out.

801
00:44:14,526 --> 00:44:15,944
Park Hae-kang.

802
00:44:16,737 --> 00:44:18,947
Do you think you've won?

803
00:44:23,619 --> 00:44:24,953
What are you waiting for?

804
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:37,675
Boss, what's going on?

805
00:44:38,300 --> 00:44:39,384
Park Hae-kang.

806
00:44:39,385 --> 00:44:42,720
You've really underestimated me.

807
00:44:42,721 --> 00:44:45,140
What are you waiting for? Crush them!

808
00:44:52,940 --> 00:44:54,565
We almost died back then.

809
00:44:54,566 --> 00:44:56,401
What do you think was the reason?

810
00:44:56,402 --> 00:44:57,528
We were too complacent.

811
00:44:58,779 --> 00:45:00,530
That was our problem.

812
00:45:00,531 --> 00:45:02,532
If we're complacent about this too,

813
00:45:02,533 --> 00:45:04,742
Jang Suk-jin could become
like the Salamander.

814
00:45:04,743 --> 00:45:06,536
We have to crush her before then.

815
00:45:06,537 --> 00:45:09,706
I'll crush Jang Suk-jin myself.

816
00:45:11,708 --> 00:45:14,545
You can't even stand up.
What could you possibly do?

817
00:45:15,045 --> 00:45:16,462
Let him go and get some exercise.

818
00:45:16,463 --> 00:45:17,464
Hey!

819
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:19,299
What is it?

820
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:21,926
Academic fraud.

821
00:45:21,927 --> 00:45:25,639
Nothing is more serious
than academic fraud in Korea.

822
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:27,516
Let's go with this.

823
00:45:28,892 --> 00:45:30,727
Academic fraud…

824
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,567
REPORTING JANG SUK-JIN'S ACADEMIC FRAUD

825
00:45:37,276 --> 00:45:40,445
But what if she really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University?

826
00:45:40,446 --> 00:45:42,697
I told you about negative campaigns.

827
00:45:42,698 --> 00:45:44,907
It doesn't matter
whether it's true or not.

828
00:45:44,908 --> 00:45:47,953
The point is to make it into a scandal.

829
00:45:48,704 --> 00:45:49,621
Right.

830
00:45:54,835 --> 00:45:56,252
REPORTING JANG SUK-JIN'S ACADEMIC FRAUD

831
00:45:56,253 --> 00:45:58,004
<i>What? Is this true?</i>

832
00:45:58,005 --> 00:45:59,547
<i>She's unbelievable.</i>

833
00:45:59,548 --> 00:46:01,382
<i>Shouldn't she withdraw her candidacy?</i>

834
00:46:01,383 --> 00:46:02,467
<i>Academic fraud over this?</i>

835
00:46:02,468 --> 00:46:03,968
<i>What is she even doing at her age?</i>

836
00:46:03,969 --> 00:46:06,054
<i>We can't have someone like her
as our building rep.</i>

837
00:46:08,223 --> 00:46:10,475
Write at least ten comments
under different usernames.

838
00:46:10,476 --> 00:46:11,435
- Okay.
- Yes, Boss.

839
00:46:12,102 --> 00:46:12,936
And the Lizard?

840
00:46:21,695 --> 00:46:24,030
How can you not know?

841
00:46:24,031 --> 00:46:27,575
You're the management office.
That doesn't make sense.

842
00:46:27,576 --> 00:46:31,204
Ma'am, it's an anonymous board
for a reason.

843
00:46:31,205 --> 00:46:32,705
We can't know who wrote it either.

844
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:34,832
Hey. I promise,

845
00:46:34,833 --> 00:46:38,586
I won't tell anyone I heard it
from the management office.

846
00:46:38,587 --> 00:46:42,089
So you can just tell me.

847
00:46:42,090 --> 00:46:43,424
Ma'am.

848
00:46:43,425 --> 00:46:45,718
No matter how much you pester us,

849
00:46:45,719 --> 00:46:47,012
we really have no idea.

850
00:46:47,638 --> 00:46:49,305
What do you mean?

851
00:46:49,306 --> 00:46:50,389
You have stuff like

852
00:46:50,390 --> 00:46:52,350
IP tracking or whatever.

853
00:46:52,351 --> 00:46:54,186
You can find them if you do that!

854
00:46:54,895 --> 00:46:57,898
We're not the police.
We can't do stuff like that.

855
00:46:58,482 --> 00:47:01,150
Fine. Then call the cops.

856
00:47:01,151 --> 00:47:02,860
Report this to the cops!

857
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:06,364
Call the National Forensic Service too.
I can't stand this.

858
00:47:06,365 --> 00:47:08,366
This is so unfair!

859
00:47:08,367 --> 00:47:09,784
Come on…

860
00:47:09,785 --> 00:47:11,327
Why are they doing this to me?

861
00:47:11,328 --> 00:47:12,453
Ma'am.

862
00:47:12,454 --> 00:47:14,497
Mr. Choi, I'm innocent.

863
00:47:14,498 --> 00:47:17,083
I really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University.

864
00:47:17,084 --> 00:47:19,544
Ma'am, just calm down first.

865
00:47:19,545 --> 00:47:21,254
If you explain to everyone

866
00:47:21,255 --> 00:47:23,881
that you really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University,

867
00:47:23,882 --> 00:47:25,634
- they'll understand.
- Mr. Choi.

868
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:28,678
- I know.
- Know what?

869
00:47:28,679 --> 00:47:30,097
I know who did this.

870
00:47:31,181 --> 00:47:34,308
I just don't have clear evidence,
but I have a hunch.

871
00:47:34,309 --> 00:47:37,104
- I know who did it.
- Who is it?

872
00:47:37,980 --> 00:47:40,524
It's Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

873
00:47:43,235 --> 00:47:46,028
He's trying to defeat me in the election.

874
00:47:46,029 --> 00:47:48,531
This is all his doing! It was his scheme!

875
00:47:48,532 --> 00:47:49,825
ACADEMIC AWARD, SCHOLARSHIP AWARD

876
00:47:56,623 --> 00:47:59,000
<i>Ma'am, I didn't just graduate.</i>

877
00:47:59,001 --> 00:48:01,294
I was at the top of my class.

878
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:02,461
- You hear?
- All right.

879
00:48:02,462 --> 00:48:04,005
I'll call you!

880
00:48:04,006 --> 00:48:07,758
- Hello.
- Please read this. I'm a victim.

881
00:48:07,759 --> 00:48:09,468
They spread lies about me.

882
00:48:09,469 --> 00:48:11,387
- I'm so upset.
- Right.

883
00:48:11,388 --> 00:48:13,014
Please just read this.

884
00:48:13,015 --> 00:48:14,056
Come on!

885
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:16,351
Why would you throw it away?

886
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:23,066
Why did he throw it away?

887
00:48:26,778 --> 00:48:28,155
I said I can go alone.

888
00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:31,449
Won't people think it's strange
if they see a mother

889
00:48:31,450 --> 00:48:33,160
heading out alone late at night?

890
00:48:33,660 --> 00:48:36,037
Just act like we're taking a walk together

891
00:48:36,038 --> 00:48:39,332
and slip out quietly
through the back gate.

892
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:40,834
Why are you so meticulous?

893
00:48:42,669 --> 00:48:43,794
We'll look like strangers.

894
00:48:43,795 --> 00:48:45,756
Just hold onto my arm.

895
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:50,009
Married couples don't normally
walk like that, you know.

896
00:48:50,010 --> 00:48:52,095
It's more natural to walk apart
like strangers.

897
00:48:52,888 --> 00:48:53,764
Ms. Kang.

898
00:48:55,265 --> 00:48:58,226
Don't you remember the clause
in our contract

899
00:48:58,727 --> 00:48:59,686
about active cooperation?

900
00:49:01,438 --> 00:49:04,191
Don't you see how cooperative I am
even while walking?

901
00:49:07,944 --> 00:49:09,071
Just hold my arm.

902
00:49:23,919 --> 00:49:24,795
Peek-a-boo!

903
00:49:30,175 --> 00:49:33,135
After all that education I gave you,

904
00:49:33,136 --> 00:49:34,680
you still don't salute me?

905
00:49:37,474 --> 00:49:39,725
Are your knees broken?
You're still sitting?

906
00:49:39,726 --> 00:49:42,311
How rude, greeting me sitting down.

907
00:49:42,312 --> 00:49:44,314
Let me give you a proper education today.

908
00:49:47,317 --> 00:49:48,402
Wait.

909
00:49:49,069 --> 00:49:50,195
What's he doing?

910
00:49:51,613 --> 00:49:52,905
Just go home, Ms. Kang.

911
00:49:52,906 --> 00:49:54,657
I will.

912
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:55,784
But first…

913
00:49:56,910 --> 00:49:58,120
That asshole!

914
00:49:58,912 --> 00:50:00,413
Let go of me!

915
00:50:00,414 --> 00:50:02,124
That asshole is a voter too.

916
00:50:02,749 --> 00:50:04,625
It won't look good for a candidate's wife

917
00:50:04,626 --> 00:50:06,628
to fight with a voter.

918
00:50:08,505 --> 00:50:11,383
A voter? Seriously?
Is building rep that important?

919
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:13,342
Mr. Park.

920
00:50:13,343 --> 00:50:15,803
You might become
the building representative this way,

921
00:50:15,804 --> 00:50:18,056
but you're hopeless as a human being.

922
00:50:24,062 --> 00:50:25,479
Mr. Park, wait.

923
00:50:25,480 --> 00:50:26,939
Hang on!

924
00:50:26,940 --> 00:50:29,275
Go home if you want
the rest of your money.

925
00:50:29,276 --> 00:50:30,609
Didn't you see him getting hit?

926
00:50:30,610 --> 00:50:32,445
I'm choosing not to see it.

927
00:50:32,446 --> 00:50:33,321
Go.

928
00:50:35,157 --> 00:50:36,074
Mr. Park!

929
00:50:42,497 --> 00:50:44,040
He's the asshole.

930
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:49,211
Do you even know who I am?

931
00:50:49,212 --> 00:50:53,048
I was the boss of the Oasis Gang,
you idiot!

932
00:50:53,049 --> 00:50:54,467
Why won't you salute me?

933
00:50:54,468 --> 00:50:55,844
You're dead!

934
00:50:57,512 --> 00:50:59,473
You're dead today.

935
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:01,808
Stop!

936
00:51:02,893 --> 00:51:04,059
And who are you?

937
00:51:04,060 --> 00:51:06,854
Get lost. I'm going to take care
of this idiot and go home.

938
00:51:06,855 --> 00:51:08,147
Me too.

939
00:51:08,148 --> 00:51:09,816
I'd like to hurry home too.

940
00:51:10,442 --> 00:51:12,777
But someone told me
I was hopeless as a human being,

941
00:51:12,778 --> 00:51:14,111
and I can't shake it off.

942
00:51:14,112 --> 00:51:16,614
What are you saying?
Is this a monologue or what?

943
00:51:16,615 --> 00:51:18,199
Do you know who I am?

944
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:20,075
You said you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang.

945
00:51:20,076 --> 00:51:22,203
Right. Do you have a death wish?

946
00:51:22,204 --> 00:51:23,997
You've never seen his face before,
have you?

947
00:51:24,748 --> 00:51:25,582
Would you like to?

948
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:31,755
Look at my face properly
so you won't forget.

949
00:51:34,132 --> 00:51:36,217
Who would want to watch you
eating <i>ramyeon</i>?

950
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:37,510
This won't do.

951
00:51:37,511 --> 00:51:39,303
- Really?
- You need to eat way more.

952
00:51:39,304 --> 00:51:40,347
You're right…

953
00:51:41,640 --> 00:51:43,474
Hey, look. They're fighting.

954
00:51:43,475 --> 00:51:45,726
- Awesome!
- Film it.

955
00:51:45,727 --> 00:51:47,770
Look!

956
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:49,022
He's dead.

957
00:51:50,899 --> 00:51:51,900
Where are you going?

958
00:51:53,652 --> 00:51:55,778
Stay back!

959
00:51:55,779 --> 00:51:57,239
Where are you going? We're not done yet.

960
00:51:57,823 --> 00:51:58,824
You should apologize to him.

961
00:51:59,825 --> 00:52:00,951
You're dead.

962
00:52:01,576 --> 00:52:03,662
Come on. Come at me!

963
00:52:11,336 --> 00:52:12,379
No way.

964
00:52:13,380 --> 00:52:15,090
I guess he's kind of cool.

965
00:52:24,266 --> 00:52:26,434
What? Are you insane?

966
00:52:28,270 --> 00:52:29,271
I need to go home.

967
00:52:37,237 --> 00:52:39,613
The building rep election is tomorrow.

968
00:52:39,614 --> 00:52:42,492
Let's do our best for one more day.

969
00:52:43,702 --> 00:52:44,910
One, two, three.

970
00:52:44,911 --> 00:52:46,328
- Win-win!
- Move.

971
00:52:46,329 --> 00:52:47,538
Let's go.

972
00:52:47,539 --> 00:52:49,039
- Let's do this!
- Let's do it!

973
00:52:49,040 --> 00:52:51,333
Let's do it. Don't forget to smile.

974
00:52:51,334 --> 00:52:52,668
"Win-win"? Forget it.

975
00:52:52,669 --> 00:52:54,713
I'll take care of my own packages.

976
00:52:55,380 --> 00:52:56,839
Which building, ma'am?

977
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:58,507
- Why are you asking me that?
- Hello.

978
00:52:58,508 --> 00:53:01,093
Thank you for everything so far.

979
00:53:01,094 --> 00:53:04,222
But don't ever deliver packages
to our house again.

980
00:53:05,140 --> 00:53:07,601
We're too scared to accept any deliveries.

981
00:53:10,729 --> 00:53:12,564
Where's my package?

982
00:53:15,650 --> 00:53:16,526
Where is it?

983
00:53:20,071 --> 00:53:20,906
What's going on?

984
00:53:21,698 --> 00:53:23,157
What's happening?

985
00:53:23,158 --> 00:53:25,327
Boss, you should take a look at this.

986
00:53:25,911 --> 00:53:28,954
Someone uploaded this YouTube video
on the anonymous board.

987
00:53:28,955 --> 00:53:30,916
DOUBLE LIFE OF THE DELIVERY HERO

988
00:53:32,250 --> 00:53:34,084
It says, "Double life
of the delivery hero."

989
00:53:34,085 --> 00:53:35,879
The comments are going crazy.

990
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:39,006
"Shouldn't he withdraw his candidacy?"

991
00:53:39,007 --> 00:53:40,592
"What a double life."

992
00:53:42,093 --> 00:53:42,928
Boss.

993
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:46,097
What on earth happened last night?

994
00:54:02,572 --> 00:54:03,989
The thing is,

995
00:54:03,990 --> 00:54:05,950
Mr. Park wasn't just beating him up.

996
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:08,702
The guy was hitting the guard,
and Mr. Park saved him.

997
00:54:08,703 --> 00:54:11,830
But that video just showed
the part where he kicked him.

998
00:54:11,831 --> 00:54:14,124
Mr. Park, say something.

999
00:54:14,125 --> 00:54:15,502
This is all…

1000
00:54:17,420 --> 00:54:18,755
your fault, Ms. Kang.

1001
00:54:20,382 --> 00:54:21,257
What?

1002
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:23,425
<i>Mr. Park.</i>

1003
00:54:23,426 --> 00:54:26,845
You might become
the building representative this way,

1004
00:54:26,846 --> 00:54:28,556
but you're hopeless as a human being.

1005
00:54:29,975 --> 00:54:31,810
Why would you blame me for that?

1006
00:54:33,228 --> 00:54:36,188
Then what do we do now?

1007
00:54:36,189 --> 00:54:37,190
Are we screwed?

1008
00:54:38,274 --> 00:54:40,317
At this point,

1009
00:54:40,318 --> 00:54:43,655
we've basically lost
the building rep election.

1010
00:54:54,499 --> 00:54:56,751
Yes, this is Park…

1011
00:54:58,545 --> 00:54:59,546
What?

1012
00:55:01,089 --> 00:55:02,173
Okay.

1013
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:04,134
Where are you going?

1014
00:55:05,427 --> 00:55:07,594
Where is he off to in such a hurry?

1015
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:09,723
MYUNGJIN UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

1016
00:55:14,644 --> 00:55:15,769
What's your business, sir?

1017
00:55:15,770 --> 00:55:18,565
I'm Park Hae-kang,
Park Yong-man's guardian.

1018
00:55:27,657 --> 00:55:31,036
You didn't even knock. Mind your manners.

1019
00:55:33,455 --> 00:55:36,499
I said I didn't need my guardian.
Why did you come?

1020
00:55:37,876 --> 00:55:40,627
You didn't take your meds again?
Do you really want to die?

1021
00:55:40,628 --> 00:55:42,756
You really must have a death wish.

1022
00:55:48,470 --> 00:55:51,096
I was so startled.
I thought something happened to you.

1023
00:55:51,097 --> 00:55:53,057
Did you forget my nickname?

1024
00:55:53,058 --> 00:55:55,268
I'm the Phoenix.

1025
00:55:55,935 --> 00:55:58,104
Don't worry. I won't die.

1026
00:56:01,608 --> 00:56:03,651
You'd better keep

1027
00:56:04,277 --> 00:56:05,611
that promise.

1028
00:56:05,612 --> 00:56:07,488
Go away. Gross.

1029
00:56:07,489 --> 00:56:09,073
Let me see.

1030
00:56:09,074 --> 00:56:11,116
Let go of me. That hurts.

1031
00:56:11,117 --> 00:56:12,284
Let me see your face.

1032
00:56:12,285 --> 00:56:14,579
Don't be so touchy-feely.

1033
00:56:19,209 --> 00:56:20,126
How handsome.

1034
00:56:21,336 --> 00:56:23,253
You little brat.

1035
00:56:23,254 --> 00:56:25,547
If I weren't tied up,

1036
00:56:25,548 --> 00:56:28,301
I'd take you down…

1037
00:56:56,287 --> 00:56:57,330
You know,

1038
00:56:57,914 --> 00:57:00,499
I never thought this project would end

1039
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:02,377
with a single kick from the boss.

1040
00:57:05,630 --> 00:57:08,133
Couldn't he have tolerated some injustice?

1041
00:57:09,050 --> 00:57:10,009
Yeah.

1042
00:57:10,635 --> 00:57:12,636
He should tolerate injustice,

1043
00:57:12,637 --> 00:57:14,847
but not accept losses.

1044
00:57:14,848 --> 00:57:16,099
He's a businessman.

1045
00:57:16,683 --> 00:57:18,559
Today's the election.

1046
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:20,228
Isn't he going to go vote?

1047
00:57:21,062 --> 00:57:24,023
Wouldn't it be embarrassing
if he ends up with just his own vote?

1048
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:28,194
Well, I guess you're right.

1049
00:57:28,778 --> 00:57:29,988
Then what do we do now?

1050
00:57:31,156 --> 00:57:34,450
I'm sure he has a plan.

1051
00:57:34,451 --> 00:57:36,452
Right. He should be waking up soon.

1052
00:57:36,453 --> 00:57:37,871
Big Guy, go and prepare breakfast.

1053
00:57:38,413 --> 00:57:40,539
I'm not in the mood to cook.

1054
00:57:40,540 --> 00:57:41,875
Let's just order something.

1055
00:57:42,584 --> 00:57:45,085
Do you really think
he'd have an appetite right now?

1056
00:57:45,086 --> 00:57:46,963
He blew his chance in the election.

1057
00:57:56,556 --> 00:57:57,765
Mr. Park.

1058
00:57:59,726 --> 00:58:01,894
If you're upset
and sulking in your room all day,

1059
00:58:01,895 --> 00:58:03,687
that's your problem.

1060
00:58:03,688 --> 00:58:05,731
It's six now, so I'm heading home.

1061
00:58:05,732 --> 00:58:07,275
Seriously?

1062
00:58:08,818 --> 00:58:10,194
Well,

1063
00:58:10,195 --> 00:58:12,279
I do feel upset too.

1064
00:58:12,280 --> 00:58:13,655
But we have no choice.

1065
00:58:13,656 --> 00:58:15,407
You already lost your chance at winning,

1066
00:58:15,408 --> 00:58:18,076
so there's no need for me
to keep coming here.

1067
00:58:18,077 --> 00:58:20,245
As you know,
you're the one who caused this,

1068
00:58:20,246 --> 00:58:22,623
- so I can't return--
<i>- This is the management office.</i>

1069
00:58:22,624 --> 00:58:26,002
<i>We will now announce
the elected building representatives.</i>

1070
00:58:26,544 --> 00:58:30,339
<i>District 1, Candidate 1, Seo Gang-won.</i>

1071
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:34,259
<i>District 2, Candidate 1, Kim O-rye.</i>

1072
00:58:34,260 --> 00:58:37,971
<i>District 3, Candidate 1, Lee Seok-man.</i>

1073
00:58:37,972 --> 00:58:41,725
<i>District 4, Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.</i>

1074
00:58:41,726 --> 00:58:45,688
Uncle got elected!

1075
00:58:48,149 --> 00:58:50,108
Uncle got elected!

1076
00:58:50,109 --> 00:58:52,402
What did they just say?
Did I hear that right?

1077
00:58:52,403 --> 00:58:53,905
Hooray!

1078
00:58:57,825 --> 00:58:59,869
- Was that a hallucination?
- No.

1079
00:59:00,662 --> 00:59:02,162
"Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang."

1080
00:59:02,163 --> 00:59:04,039
I'm sure I heard it too.

1081
00:59:04,040 --> 00:59:06,000
I heard it too. Park Hae-kang.

1082
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,168
- Right?
- Right.

1083
00:59:08,169 --> 00:59:10,128
Does this make any sense?

1084
00:59:10,129 --> 00:59:12,340
Boss, take a look at this.

1085
00:59:14,592 --> 00:59:15,468
What is it?

1086
00:59:18,137 --> 00:59:19,304
<i>Hello.</i>

1087
00:59:19,305 --> 00:59:21,683
<i>I'm Oh Sang-min,
the head of security for True Value.</i>

1088
00:59:22,684 --> 00:59:25,519
<i>All the guards of True Value</i>

1089
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:29,148
<i>were assaulted multiple times
by the tattooed man in the video.</i>

1090
00:59:30,191 --> 00:59:34,194
<i>The man was assaulting
our guard Choi Su-dong,</i>

1091
00:59:34,195 --> 00:59:36,738
<i>who was on his shift alone that day.</i>

1092
00:59:36,739 --> 00:59:39,032
<i>And Mr. Park Hae-kang
was the one who helped him.</i>

1093
00:59:39,033 --> 00:59:40,743
That lunatic picked up a shovel.

1094
00:59:42,036 --> 00:59:44,121
- Great job!
- I see.

1095
00:59:44,122 --> 00:59:45,664
- How satisfying.
- I see.

1096
00:59:45,665 --> 00:59:48,667
So that's what happened!

1097
00:59:48,668 --> 00:59:52,170
<i>Of course, violence isn't a good thing,
but if Mr. Park hadn't helped,</i>

1098
00:59:52,171 --> 00:59:54,298
<i>I can't even imagine
what would have happened.</i>

1099
00:59:54,299 --> 00:59:55,465
Kneel.

1100
00:59:55,466 --> 00:59:59,219
<i>He seemed to be in a tight spot
because he was unfairly framed,</i>

1101
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:00,387
<i>so I wanted to explain.</i>

1102
01:00:00,388 --> 01:00:01,556
I'm sorry.

1103
01:00:02,390 --> 01:00:03,433
Apologize sincerely.

1104
01:00:04,559 --> 01:00:05,893
I'll move out right away!

1105
01:00:06,561 --> 01:00:08,187
- What?
- I'll move right away!

1106
01:00:08,896 --> 01:00:10,564
- Louder.
- I'll move right away!

1107
01:00:10,565 --> 01:00:13,568
<i>On behalf of all the guards
of True Value State,</i>

1108
01:00:14,444 --> 01:00:16,695
<i>I sincerely thank Mr. Park Hae-kang.</i>

1109
01:00:16,696 --> 01:00:17,738
The comments!

1110
01:00:17,739 --> 01:00:20,741
"I voted for Park Hae-kang
after reading this."

1111
01:00:20,742 --> 01:00:22,326
"I feel sorry I misunderstood him."

1112
01:00:22,327 --> 01:00:25,078
They're saying
you're not just a delivery hero,

1113
01:00:25,079 --> 01:00:26,455
but the hero of True Value!

1114
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:28,123
Congratulations.

1115
01:00:28,124 --> 01:00:29,417
You've been elected.

1116
01:00:30,043 --> 01:00:32,545
Boss, congratulations on getting elected.

1117
01:00:33,171 --> 01:00:35,965
- Our boss is the building representative!
- He did it!

1118
01:00:38,551 --> 01:00:40,053
He's the building rep!

1119
01:00:42,722 --> 01:00:45,558
We did it!

1120
01:01:25,682 --> 01:01:26,848
PARK HAE-KANG MUST BE AN ANGEL

1121
01:01:26,849 --> 01:01:28,266
HE'S THE DEFINITION OF MORALLY PURE

1122
01:01:28,267 --> 01:01:29,685
I'M SO GLAD HE LIVES HERE

1123
01:01:29,686 --> 01:01:30,977
PARK HAE-KANG IS A REAL HERO!

1124
01:01:30,978 --> 01:01:32,521
ROOTING FOR YOU, PARK HAE-KANG

1125
01:01:32,522 --> 01:01:34,106
I'VE NEVER SEEN SUCH A RELIABLE CANDIDATE

1126
01:01:34,107 --> 01:01:35,899
I'D HAVE NO COMPLAINTS
IF HE WERE BUILDING REP

1127
01:01:35,900 --> 01:01:37,276
HE SURE CAN BE TRUSTED

1128
01:02:08,307 --> 01:02:10,601
THE APARTMENT JOB

1129
01:02:34,709 --> 01:02:37,294
<i>I hear Park Hae-kang
became the building rep.</i>

1130
01:02:37,295 --> 01:02:39,045
<i>I found him quite interesting.</i>

1131
01:02:39,046 --> 01:02:41,423
<i>We all know the election
for president is coming up.</i>

1132
01:02:41,424 --> 01:02:44,176
No one else is running, right?

1133
01:02:44,177 --> 01:02:45,303
I will run as well.

1134
01:02:46,763 --> 01:02:49,723
But I can't let him succeed
in my apartment complex.

1135
01:02:49,724 --> 01:02:51,349
- You need people on your side.
<i>- My side?</i>

1136
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:54,811
<i>Like a faction. Or a support base.</i>

1137
01:02:54,812 --> 01:02:57,522
- Honey.
- "Honey"?

1138
01:02:57,523 --> 01:02:59,441
<i>Elections are all about public opinion.</i>

1139
01:02:59,442 --> 01:03:00,817
<i>You can't defeat President Seo.</i>

1140
01:03:00,818 --> 01:03:03,320
<i>But President Seo,
this has to stop at just being fun.</i>

1141
01:03:03,321 --> 01:03:04,613
<i>You understand, don't you?</i>

1142
01:03:04,614 --> 01:03:08,408
I heard you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang.

1143
01:03:08,409 --> 01:03:09,326
Gosh, it's hot!

1144
01:03:09,327 --> 01:03:10,619
<i>Will this really work, though?</i>

1145
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:13,539
<i>This is the only thing that can flip
public opinion about me in one shot.</i>

1146
01:03:14,290 --> 01:03:15,792
So dig.

1147
01:03:18,461 --> 01:03:20,463
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
